Instead of focusing the protocol around dictionaries, do it around `Config` instances because conversion to dictionary is specific to the format -- ConfigParser needs everything as string-representations, JSON probably can handle the raw value, YAML -- not sure.
```
def dump_config_to_file(config, file_obj, **kwargs)
def dump_config_to_string(config, **kwargs)
def load_config_from_file(file_obj, **kwargs)
def load_config_from_string(string, **kwargs)
```

It looks like one of us has an ordering bug with regard to pending transactions.

My understanding is the ordering in the history should be:
height, ascending
tx_hash, ascending

So in this case with a79 and e22 both pending, a79 should come first, which is what jelectrum is doing.
Electrumx seems to have it reversed.

