Is it possible to have 1 resource but to have the get, put take different url parameters?

For example:

```
@api.route('/<string:todo_id>')
class TodoSimple(Resource):
    def get(self, todo_id):
        return {todo_id: todos[todo_id]}

    def put(self, todo_id, another_param):
        todos[todo_id] = request.form['data']
        return {todo_id: todos[todo_id]}
```

The problem is that the route is on the class and it applies to all definitions of the class. And if i try to do individual routes per endpoint it breaks 

```
class TodoSimple(Resource):
    @api.route('/<string:todo_id>')
    def get(self, todo_id):
        pass

    @api.route('/<string:todo_id>,<string:another_param>')
    def put(self, todo_id, another_param):
        pass
```
I am guess i am just missing something here. any help would be appreciated.

